00:25.067 --> 00:27.600
[Voiceover] He's reaching
out, really, for the downtrodden

00:27.600 --> 00:30.933
Of society, for the average
Joe on the street who wants

00:30.933 --> 00:33.267
To look up to his lyrics
and his music and say,

00:33.267 --> 00:35.700
"Hey, this man's
talking my language."

00:43.533 --> 00:45.167
[Voiceover] You guys don't
like explaining anything

00:45.167 --> 00:46.433
To do with your music...

00:46.433 --> 00:47.367
[Voiceover] There's
nothing to be said,

00:47.367 --> 00:48.733
It's all in the music, man.

00:48.733 --> 00:50.200
It's all in the music.

00:51.333 --> 00:53.333
[Voiceover] If there was
a John Lennon-type figure

00:53.333 --> 00:56.333
For the so-called "Generation
X," it would be Cobain.

00:56.967 --> 00:58.467
[Voiceover] The body of
Nirvana leader Kurt Cobain

00:58.467 --> 01:00.767
Was found in a house in
Seattle on Friday morning,

01:00.767 --> 01:03.167
Dead of an apparently
self-inflicted shotgun blast

01:03.167 --> 01:04.667
To the head.

01:04.933 --> 01:07.533
[Voiceover] An electrician
hired to work on Cobain's home

01:07.533 --> 01:10.300
Walked up to this room
above Cobain's garage

01:10.300 --> 01:12.800
And made the shocking
discovery this morning.

01:13.267 --> 01:14.867
[Voiceover] A
suicide note was found.

01:14.867 --> 01:16.433
[Voiceover] This
is a puzzling case,

01:16.433 --> 01:18.433
A very disturbing case.

01:19.267 --> 01:22.133
[Voiceover] It first got
reported that Kurt was missing

01:22.133 --> 01:26.167
And Courtney Love hired
private investigator Tom Grant.

01:26.167 --> 01:27.100
[Voiceover] I had
been involved in

01:27.100 --> 01:29.300
Missing persons cases before.

01:29.300 --> 01:31.933
Some red flags started
popping up immediately,

01:31.933 --> 01:35.667
So I began recording every
conversation I had with Courtney

01:35.667 --> 01:38.333
During the entire period
that I worked for her.

01:38.767 --> 01:42.633
[Voiceover] My
name is (Indistinct)

01:42.633 --> 01:45.200
[Voiceover] It could be
made to look like a suicide.

01:45.200 --> 01:47.533
[Voiceover] People that
I had do this, I paid.

01:47.533 --> 01:49.067
[Voiceover] I've walked
into cases that looked

01:49.067 --> 01:51.200
Like they were suicides that
turned out to be homicides.

01:51.200 --> 01:52.767
[Voiceover] Cobain's
wife, singer Courtney Love,

01:52.767 --> 01:54.867
Was in England on tour
with her band Hole

01:54.867 --> 01:56.300
When the body was discovered.

01:56.300 --> 01:58.200
[Voiceover] As it is,
she has inherited an estate

01:58.200 --> 02:00.167
Worth tens of
millions of dollars.

02:00.167 --> 02:01.567
That's motive.

02:01.567 --> 02:02.933
[Voiceover] Did Courtney
Love kill Kurt Cobain?

02:02.933 --> 02:05.833
Did she have a hand in
any kind of conspiracy?

02:05.833 --> 02:10.800
These are favorite
topics of fanatics.

02:11.733 --> 02:13.633
[Voiceover] There's nothing
in the medical examiner's

02:13.633 --> 02:16.500
Report or coroner's reports
that could not have easily

02:16.500 --> 02:18.867
Have been duplicated
by a murderer.

02:18.867 --> 02:21.267
[Voiceover] It's entirely
possible that a police officer,

02:21.267 --> 02:24.967
No matter how well-trained,
may not see or notice

02:24.967 --> 02:27.133
A particular item of evidence.

02:27.133 --> 02:29.133
[Voiceover] Kurt
Cobain was not barricaded

02:29.133 --> 02:30.367
Inside the room.

02:30.367 --> 02:32.600
He did not leave his
driver's license out.

02:32.600 --> 02:34.800
No one would believe
that was a suicide note.

02:34.800 --> 02:36.933
Kurt Cobain was injected
with three times

02:36.933 --> 02:39.533
The lethal dose of heroin.

02:39.533 --> 02:41.500
The media was
getting this wrong.

