08:21.167 --> 08:22.833
My name is Tom Grant.

08:22.833 --> 08:25.067
I was hired by Courtney
Love to find her missing

08:25.067 --> 08:29.067
Husband, Kurt Cobain,
in April of 1994.

08:32.167 --> 08:35.467
My father was a schoolteacher,

08:35.467 --> 08:39.133
And this is a man I
never caught one time

08:39.133 --> 08:41.533
In my entire life telling a lie.

08:42.600 --> 08:46.467
He was the best role
model anybody can ask for.

08:47.867 --> 08:50.800
By the time I became a
junior in high school,

08:50.800 --> 08:53.967
I definitely wanted to
be a police officer.

08:54.733 --> 08:57.067
Graduating from the L.A.
County Sheriff's Department

08:57.067 --> 09:01.067
Was a very proud day for
me and for my family.

09:01.600 --> 09:04.067
My first assignment
was a patrol division

09:04.067 --> 09:06.700
At West Hollywood
Sheriff Station.

09:10.500 --> 09:14.133
When I quit the department,
I quit in very high standing.

09:14.133 --> 09:15.967
From there I moved
on, took the test

09:15.967 --> 09:19.167
And obtained my own private
investigator's license.

09:26.133 --> 09:30.267
I believe what makes me a good
P.I. is that I always apply

09:30.267 --> 09:33.867
Logic and common sense
to everything that I do.

09:35.133 --> 09:38.933
I've seen a lot of
suicides, a lot of murders,

09:38.933 --> 09:42.067
And I don't try to
pre-determine anything.

09:43.533 --> 09:46.067
And if I feel that my
client, that's coming to me

09:46.067 --> 09:50.267
For help, is in the wrong based
on what they're telling me,

09:50.267 --> 09:52.600
I'll let them know,
"This could be a pretty"

09:52.600 --> 09:54.867
"Dangerous trip for you."

09:54.867 --> 09:57.733
Scratch the surface of most
P.I.s and you don't find a clean

09:57.733 --> 10:00.000
Record, you find
a lotta skeletons.

10:00.000 --> 10:01.600
And then we met Tom Grant.

10:01.600 --> 10:04.100
It turned out he had
an exemplary record.

10:04.100 --> 10:06.967
He was respected, he
was a stand-up guy.

10:06.967 --> 10:09.500
There was a consensus,
and that went a long way

10:09.500 --> 10:12.467
To convincing us
of his credibility.

10:12.467 --> 10:15.400
The word conspiracy is
actually a legal term.

10:15.400 --> 10:18.733
It simply means two or
more people plotting

10:18.733 --> 10:21.367
Or planning to commit a crime.

10:21.367 --> 10:24.467
Even committing shoplifting
with another person

10:24.467 --> 10:27.467
Can actually be charged
with conspiracy.

10:28.300 --> 10:31.500
When somebody refers to me
as a conspiracy theorist,

10:31.500 --> 10:35.133
I take it as an insult because
I know what they mean by it.

10:35.833 --> 10:38.833
Hiring me is not like
hiring an attorney.

10:38.833 --> 10:43.100
It's not to protect you, it's
not to keep you outta jail.

10:43.100 --> 10:46.500
My job as a private investigator
is to find the truth.

10:46.500 --> 10:49.633
It's simply to find
the truth in the matter

10:49.633 --> 10:51.967
That you're hiring me for.

10:54.900 --> 10:59.900
(Eerie music)

11:03.267 --> 11:06.367
On Easter Sunday,
I was in my office

11:06.367 --> 11:09.067
With a private investigator
who worked for me

11:09.067 --> 11:11.200
Named Ben Klugman,
and we were dealing

11:11.200 --> 11:14.167
With a client when
the phone rang.

11:14.167 --> 11:15.700
(Phone ringing)

11:15.700 --> 11:16.967
Now who calls on Easter?

11:16.967 --> 11:19.500
Would you excuse us
for just a second?

11:20.533 --> 11:22.400
The Grant Company,
how may I help you?

11:22.400 --> 11:24.867
[Tom] And it was a woman's
voice on the other end,

11:24.867 --> 11:26.700
Kind of a raspy, low voice.

11:26.700 --> 11:29.167
Now if someone is unlawfully
using your credit cards,

11:29.167 --> 11:31.667
Maybe the police are the
better people to call.

11:31.667 --> 11:34.233
[Tom] And then she said,
"My husband and I are"

11:34.233 --> 11:38.267
"Kinda famous, and we need
to get this done right away."

11:39.933 --> 11:41.233
And your husband's name?

11:41.233 --> 11:42.567
Are you kidding me?

11:42.567 --> 11:43.833
No, no.

11:43.833 --> 11:46.067
I was about 47 at
the time; Ben Klugman,

11:46.067 --> 11:48.133
My investigator, was 29.

11:48.133 --> 11:50.333
He immediately
knew who they were

11:50.333 --> 11:53.600
And what had been
going on, even in Rome

11:53.600 --> 11:55.233
Just a few weeks earlier.

11:55.233 --> 11:57.833
Because it was a holiday, of
course, there were very few,

11:57.833 --> 12:00.967
If any, other
private investigators
working, so she went

12:00.967 --> 12:03.233
Through the Yellow Pages
and she found our ad

12:03.233 --> 12:06.367
And I was probably one
of many that she called,

12:06.367 --> 12:07.833
And I think she was
probably surprised

12:07.833 --> 12:09.767
To have the phone picked up.

12:09.767 --> 12:11.300
What room number?

12:12.067 --> 12:15.067
It's not very often that
a private investigator goes

12:15.067 --> 12:18.933
Against his client, so I'm
sure she regrets hiring me.

12:22.267 --> 12:24.100
When we were available
to meet Courtney

12:24.100 --> 12:27.633
At the Peninsula Hotel,
first thing she said,

12:27.633 --> 12:30.100
And this is her words,
they're not mine,

12:32.933 --> 12:37.200
You leak this to the press,
I'll sue the fuck out of you.

12:38.833 --> 12:41.500
Well, hello to
you too. (Laughing)

12:41.500 --> 12:43.167
How ya doin'?

12:46.067 --> 12:48.133
Kurtis came from
rehab a couple days ago.

12:48.133 --> 12:49.833
He bought a ticket back to
Seattle, but nobody's seen him

12:49.833 --> 12:51.267
Since he got back.

12:51.267 --> 12:53.267
When I first entered
the room, she was wearing

12:53.267 --> 12:58.067
A negligee nightgown,
totally see-through.

12:58.067 --> 13:01.700
She might as well have
had nothing on whatsoever.

13:04.067 --> 13:05.267
[Courtney] I called
the credit card companies

13:05.267 --> 13:07.333
And told them that
the card was stolen

13:07.333 --> 13:09.067
And that they should cancel it.

13:11.233 --> 13:12.333
[Tom] Was it?

13:12.900 --> 13:14.067
[Courtney] What?

13:15.067 --> 13:16.533
[Tom] Stolen.

13:16.533 --> 13:18.067
[Courtney] No.

13:18.567 --> 13:21.400
Courtney eventually told
us that Kurt's credit card

13:21.400 --> 13:24.067
Actually wasn't stolen,
that she had called the

13:24.067 --> 13:27.633
Credit card company and
canceled it so that nobody

13:27.633 --> 13:29.067
Could use it.

13:29.067 --> 13:31.600
She felt that that would,
essentially, cut him off

13:31.600 --> 13:33.800
From any funds.

13:34.400 --> 13:36.433
I'm sure your husband has
another way of getting money.

13:36.433 --> 13:37.800
[Courtney] Are you kidding me?

13:37.800 --> 13:39.700
Kurt is helpless, he
doesn't have any friends.

13:39.700 --> 13:42.300
Again, in her words,
"You don't understand."

13:42.300 --> 13:43.567
"This guy can't even catch a..."

13:43.567 --> 13:46.100
Fucking cab by
himself if he wanted to!

13:46.833 --> 13:47.600
[Woman] Hey.

13:47.600 --> 13:48.800
[Courtney] Hey.

13:56.933 --> 13:58.600
That's my drug dealer.

14:00.600 --> 14:02.300
I didn't know at the
time that this was supposed

14:02.300 --> 14:04.933
To be an in-house rehab.

14:04.933 --> 14:08.667
I learned that later,
but a total farce.

14:08.667 --> 14:10.800
Most of the time I was
with her, she was either

14:10.800 --> 14:13.667
On drugs or doing drugs.

14:13.667 --> 14:16.333
There was nobody overseeing
what was going on there.

14:16.333 --> 14:18.600
[Courtney] Listen,
Kurt escaped from rehab,

14:18.600 --> 14:21.367
He bought a shotgun, and I
just feel like something bad

14:21.367 --> 14:22.900
Is gonna happen, okay?

14:22.900 --> 14:25.533
In the middle of all this
conversation, she keeps talking

14:25.533 --> 14:28.100
About how suicidal he is,
and how everybody thinks

14:28.100 --> 14:29.800
He's gonna commit suicide.

14:29.800 --> 14:30.867
[Courtney] Everybody
knows it, everybody thinks

14:30.867 --> 14:31.867
He's gonna die.

14:31.867 --> 14:33.067
Hold on a second.

14:33.067 --> 14:35.067
If he bought a shotgun
and he's suicidal,

14:35.067 --> 14:36.567
Then dealing with this
credit card problem,

14:36.567 --> 14:39.200
That's the least important
thing we could help you with.

14:39.867 --> 14:43.233
[Courtney] Okay, well that's
where I want you to start.

14:45.067 --> 14:47.867
She started off with a lie
when we first talked to her

14:47.867 --> 14:50.867
On the phone, saying why
she wanted to hire us,

14:50.867 --> 14:54.233
Which wasn't true, and
then she starts telling us

14:54.233 --> 14:56.267
These other things that
just didn't add up.

14:56.267 --> 14:58.733
They weren't logical,
they didn't make sense.

14:58.733 --> 15:01.733
So all kinds of red
flags started popping up.

15:01.733 --> 15:03.100
I dunno what's gonna
happen with this case,

15:03.100 --> 15:05.933
But we are gonna
document everything.

15:06.567 --> 15:09.067
Looking back on that day,
it turned out to be a day

15:09.067 --> 15:13.533
That really changed
my life forever.

15:13.533 --> 15:16.200
The name Kurt Cobain
goes through my mind,

15:16.200 --> 15:19.900
Probably three or 400
times a day, at least,

15:19.900 --> 15:24.100
And it has for the last
20 years, by necessity,

15:24.100 --> 15:26.633
Because of the e-mails I
get, the letters I get,

15:26.633 --> 15:29.933
And all the other stuff,
because he was so famous,

15:29.933 --> 15:33.900
And it gets a little
bit old after a while,

15:33.900 --> 15:36.067
Just thinking Kurt Cobain,
Kurt Cobain, Kurt Cobain.

15:36.067 --> 15:38.067
[Voiceover] Kurt Cobain,
Kurt Cobain, Kurt Cobain,

15:38.067 --> 15:39.833
Kurt Cobain, Kurt Cobain.

15:39.833 --> 15:44.833
(Rock music)

